Register for our birdwatching workshop today! We’ll be doing a hands-on birdwatching adventure June 4th at Creek Park with Environmental Educator Amy Simso Dean! Participants will learn how to spot and identify birds using easy field marks, behavior, calls, and songs. All experiences levels and abilities are welcome. The Friends of the Library are having their Spring Book Sale April 20-26. Stop by any time the library is open to purchase gently used books and DVDs. All items are $1 or less! April 25-26 is a bag sale, with all the items you can fit in a bag for $2. The next book […]

Our 2nd Annual Tiny Art Show has begun! Stop by all through February to view the tiny canvases and tiny sculptures that our patrons have created. Really love a piece of artwork? Leave a note for the artist to let them know you appreciate their work.
